-- UBS Asia-Pacific Equities Head Beshke to Retire, Memo Says
-- B y   B e i   H u
-- 2013-05-10T08:23:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-10/ubs-asia-pacific-equities-head-beshke-to-retire-memo-says.html
C.J. Beshke,  UBS AG (UBSN) ’s head of Asia-Pacific equities, will retire after 24 years with the largest
Swiss bank, according to an internal memo distributed yesterday.  The Zurich-based bank has  named  Shane Gunther and Taichi
Takahashi as co-heads of the business, Chi-Won Yoon, Asia-Pacific chief executive officer, and Mike Stewart, head of
global equities, said in the document obtained by Bloomberg
News. Both are based in Hong Kong.  Mark Panday, a Hong Kong-based spokesman for the bank,
confirmed the content of the memo.  Beshke, who joined O’Connor & Associates in  Chicago  as a
trading assistant in 1989, has been based in Hong Kong since
1996. He held positions including head of equity trading in the
region before the latest job.  Gunther was head of cash sales for the Asia-Pacific region.
He led the research teams in Thailand and  Japan , and headed
Japan equity sales after joining the bank in 1999.  Takahashi was most recently co-head of equities trading in
the region. He also led the bank’s Japan trading team and was a
co-head and head of Japan equities after joining the bank in
1994.  To contact the reporter on this story:
